about blood. As such, the authors offer new entryways into thinking about politics and economy through a "bloodscape of difference": different sovereignties; different proportionalities; and different temporalities. These entryways allow the authors to explore the relation between blood's utopic flows and political clottings as it moves through time and space, conjuring new kinds of social collectivities while reanimating older forms, and always in a reflexive relation to norms that guide its proper flow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aBlood donorszIndia, North. 0aBlood donorszIndia. 0aBloodxCollection and preservationzIndia, North. 0aBloodxCollection and preservationzIndia. 0aBloodxPolitical aspectszIndia. 0aBloodxSocial aspectszIndia, North. 0aBloodxSocial aspectszIndia. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 7aMEDICAL / Hematology.2bisacsh  apolitical substances, South Asia, Religious Nationalism, Moral Materialism, Medicine.1 aBanerjee, Dwaipayan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501745102zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501745102423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501745102.jpg  a